                  <section>
                    <title>Has the Apple bubble burst?</title>
                    <chapter>
                      <paragraph>On 26th April afternoon, Apple reported that its sales
                        and profit both fell last quarter, a rarity for a company that
                        has been growing at a rapid race, even as it has become
                        the largest technology company on the planet. More than two-thirds
                        of Apple’s revenue is made up of iPhone sales. So where the iPhone goes,
                        so goes Apple - and last quarter was a miserable one for Apple’s signature gadget.
                        IPhone sales fell for the first time in history. Apple is running out of
                        new people to buy iPhones. Phone sales been hurt by economic troubles in
                        country like Russia, Brazil and China. So Apple is looking for new ways to get more iphone sales.
                        Sales in all regions fell, but none more than in China. China is
                        particularly worrisome for Apple because it has risen quite quickly
                        to become Apple’s second-most important region. There iBooks and iTunes
                        Movies services have been shut down by government.</paragraph>
                      </chapter>
